Former Multimedia University student, who went missing and her body found at a city mortuary, was hit by a speeding vehicle, a post-mortem report reveals. The examination conducted on Susan Njoki indicated that she had a broken skull and fractured limbs indicating she was most likely involved in road accident. The examination was conducted on Wednesday at the City Mortuary before the body was moved to her rural home in Njoro. The body arrived at Egerton University mortuary on Wednesday evening where it was preserved as the family continue with burial arrangements. Ms Njoki's brother Suleiman Muiruri Ngugi said that the burial is set for Friday at her parentsâ€™ home in Jordan estate, Njoro.   Multimedia University graduate went missing last year on December 30.